Mälarenergi is certified according to Schysst Elhandel. It means we have committed to 18 customer promises. These customer promises relate to everything from clear and accurate price information to special consideration for vulnerable customers in the sales process. The customer promises go further than the law requires, and they have been established to make it easier for the customer to feel assured in their choice of electricity contract. On the Swedenergy website you can see which companies are certified (in Swedish only):
Reduced Swedish nuclear power because the Ringhals 4 nuclear power reactor is out of operation.
Frequently asked questions about the electricity market
Electricity prices are affected by the supply and demand of electricity, which in turn are affected by several factors.
It is always better to make an active choice of electricity contract. If you do not make an active choice, you will be given a temporary monthly or designated price.
2.      Monitor the
spot price
Why are electricity prices so high?
! The spot price affects you if you have a variable hourly rate and variable electricity price. The spot price does not affect our fixed electricity price contracts, since these are priced on a futures market and not on the Nord Pool electricity exchange.
Frequently asked questions about the electricity market | Mälarenergi
Soumeksi:
If you want to know exactly what the price will be per kWh, you should choose a fixed electricity contract – but it is then important to be aware that the price will be valid for the entire contract period, regardless of how market prices develop in the meantime.
On the other hand, if we have a cold winter with little wind, electricity prices will probably remain at high levels, or even increase.
“You can get a low electricity price with us if you provide a deposit”. Electricity prices are high at all electricity trading companies right now, not just at Mälarenergi. If you get an offer that sounds too good to be true, it probably is.
